Definition 2.8. Let $(\mathcal{S},\mathcal{T}),(\mathcal{U},\mathcal{V})$ be a twin cotorsion pair on $\mathscr{C}$. We define subcategories of $\mathscr{C}$ by $\mathcal{W}=\mathcal{T}\cap\mathcal{U},\ \ \mathscr{C}^{-}=\mathcal{S}[-1]\ast% \mathcal{W},\ \ \mathscr{C}^{+}=\mathcal{W}\ast\mathcal{V}[1],\ \ \mathcal{H}=% \mathscr{C}^{+}\cap\mathscr{C}^{-}.$ Each of $\mathscr{C},\mathscr{C}^{+},\mathscr{C}^{-},\mathcal{H}$ contains $\mathcal{W}$ as a subcategory. We denote their ideal quotients by $\mathcal{W}$ by $\underline{\mathscr{C}},\underline{\mathscr{C}}^{+},\underline{\mathscr{C}}^{-% },\underline{\mathcal{H}}$. Thus we obtain a sequence of full additive subcategories $\underline{\mathcal{H}}\subseteq\underline{\mathscr{C}}^{+}\subseteq\underline% {\mathscr{C}},\quad\underline{\mathcal{H}}\subseteq\underline{\mathscr{C}}^{-}% \subseteq\underline{\mathscr{C}}.$ For any morphism $f\in\mathscr{C}(A,B)$, we denote its image in $\underline{\mathscr{C}}(A,B)$ by $\underline{f}$.
